verses.text: Unto thee lift I \w up|strong="H5375"\w* mine \w eyes|strong="H5869"\w*, O thou that \w dwellest|strong="H3427"\w* in the \w heavens|strong="H8064"\w*.

Behold, as the \w eyes|strong="H5869"\w* of \w servants|strong="H5650"\w* \add look\add* unto the \w hand|strong="H3027"\w* of their \w masters|strong="H0113"\w*, \add and\add* as the \w eyes|strong="H5869"\w* of a \w maiden|strong="H8198"\w* unto the \w hand|strong="H3027"\w* of her \w mistress|strong="H1404"\w*; so our \w eyes|strong="H5869"\w* \add wait\add* upon the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* our \w God|strong="H0430"\w*, until that he have \w mercy|strong="H2603"\w* upon us.

Have \w mercy|strong="H2603"\w* upon us, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, have \w mercy|strong="H2603"\w* upon us: for we are \w exceedingly|strong="H7227"\w* \w filled|strong="H7646"\w* with \w contempt|strong="H0937"\w*.

Our \w soul|strong="H5315"\w* is \w exceedingly|strong="H7227"\w* \w filled|strong="H7646"\w* with the \w scorning|strong="H3933"\w* of those that are at \w ease|strong="H7600"\w*, \add and\add* with the \w contempt|strong="H0937"\w* of the \w proud|strong="H3238"\w*.
